## Material semantics (shell infrastructure)

Authority order: `app/globals.css` → ADR-0001 §13 → AGENTS §7. If they diverge, `globals.css` + ADR win — fix this rule in the same change.

> Material is **shell infrastructure** — not generic UI styling. Buttons, forms, tables, ERP content stay `opaque`. Cognition is **not** a reading layer.

### Four phases (only these exist)

| Phase | Class | When |
|---|---|---|
| `shell` | `.af-material-shell` | Idle, settled — default for chrome |
| `transition` | `.af-material-transition` | Activation threshold |
| `cognition` | `.af-material-cognition` | Truth resolution (Lynx active) |
| `cognition+` | shell + `data-lynx="high-confidence"` | Confidence-deepened cognition |
| opaque | `.af-material-opaque` | Dense reading surfaces — **required** for tables, ledgers, audit logs, ERP forms |

### `data-phase` state machine (canonical values only)

```
idle → hover → focus → typing → resolving → execution → settled
```

Forbidden ad-hoc names: `active`, `selected`, `open`, `loading`, `processing`, `ai`, `aiActive`.

### `data-lynx` vocabulary

| Value | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `idle` | shell |
| `listening` | transition |
| `resolving` | cognition |
| `high-confidence` | deeper saturation |
| `warning` / `mismatch` | pressure pulse / unstable refraction |

Banned user-facing labels: **AI mode**, **AI active**, **Thinking**, **Processing**, **Generating**. Use: `resolving`, `listening`, `high confidence`, `warning`, `mismatch`.

### Surface adoption matrix

| Surface | Allowed material |
|---|---|
| Utility bar (L1) | `shell` only |
| Dock (L4) | `shell` + `current` |
| Command palette (L3) | `shell → transition → cognition` |
| Lynx resolution surfaces | `cognition` (via `data-lynx`) |
| Modals, toasts | `shell` or `transition` |
| Dense tables / ledgers / audit logs | `opaque` only |
| ERP forms | `opaque` or light `shell` |

### Forbidden patterns (CI-enforced outside `app/globals.css`)

```ts
// ❌ inline style — bypasses material governance
style={{ backdropFilter: "blur(20px)" }}
style={{ willChange: "backdrop-filter" }}
```
```html
<!-- ❌ arbitrary blur — bypasses 3-tier budget -->
<div className="backdrop-blur-[18px]" />
<div className="blur-[24px]" />
<!-- ❌ scaled backdrop-blur under components/nexus/ -->
<div className="backdrop-blur-2xl" />
```
```css
/* ❌ permanent motion — cognitive fatigue */
animation: pulse 2s ease infinite;
```

Also forbidden (renamed identifiers — drift detector):
- `--af-water-*` → use `--af-cognition-*` / `--af-resolution-*`
- `.af-material-water` → `.af-material-cognition`
- `.af-material-transitioning` → `.af-material-transition`

### Nexus chrome utilities (`components/nexus/` only)

Use these CSS helpers — do **not** use Tailwind `backdrop-blur-*`:
- `.af-nexus-l1-chrome-backplate` (L1 shell-tier glass tint + blur; pair `.af-nexus-utility-bar-backdrop` on bar)
- `.af-nexus-popover-panel` (floating panels → command tier)
- `.af-nexus-round-control-backdrop` (icon-only round controls)

### Animation discipline

- State pulses fire **3 iterations on entry, then settle**.
- Persistent state: communicate via **static styling** (`outline`, `border-color`), never infinite animation.
- All animations respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`.

